
= checkbox_demo: labeled check box =

This is an editor for a true/false data field where the editor is a
checkbox that is labeled with the yes/no text.

When the checkbox is toggled, the text changes to show the text that
would be shown when the editor is removed.

== Features ==

Submit: on a blur event.

Send: value is 1 for checked, 0 for unchecked.

Cancel: can not be cancelled.

== Data ==
Can set a list of two items. The first represents no/false, and the
second represents yes/true.

The default list is "No", "Yes".

== Options ==
Buttons allowed: no.
